  • If frozen, thaw the shrimp (see the notes above).
  • Mince the garlic.
  • Pat the shrimp dry.
  • In a medium bowl, mix the shrimp with the garlic and salt.
  • In a large skillet, heat the butter on medium high heat.
  • Cook the shrimp for 1 to 2 minutes per side until opaque and cooked through, turning them with tongs.
  • Spritz with juice of the lemon wedges and serve immediately.
